  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the process to get a job at Wipro?",
  "response": "The process to get a job at Wipro generally involves several steps, which may vary slightly depending on the position and region. Here\u2019s a typical recruitment process:\n\n1. **Application:**\n   - Visit Wipro\u2019s careers page or job portals where they list vacancies.\n   - Search for a suitable job opening based on your skills, experience, and interests.\n   - Submit your application by filling out the required details and uploading your resume.\n\n2. **Screening:**\n   - Wipro\u2019s HR team will screen resumes to shortlist candidates who meet the job criteria.\n   - Shortlisted candidates may be contacted for an initial phone or video interview.\n\n3. **Assessment:**\n   - Depending on the role, you may be required to complete an online assessment test. This could include aptitude tests, technical tests, logical reasoning, and possibly coding challenges for technical roles.\n\n4. **Interviews:**\n   - There could be multiple rounds of interviews, including:\n     - **Technical Interviews:** Focused on your technical skills and problem-solving abilities. These may involve technical questions, coding exercises, or discussions about past projects.\n     - **HR Interview:** Evaluates your personality, communication skills, cultural fit, and alignment with the company\u2019s values.\n     - **Managerial Interview:** Sometimes included to assess your experience, decision-making ability, and how you handle work situations.\n\n5. **Offer:**\n   - If you succeed in the interviews, Wipro will extend a job offer. This will include details about salary, job role, location, and other terms of employment.\n\n6. **Background Verification:**\n   - Wipro may conduct a thorough background check to verify your educational qualifications, past employment, and other credentials.\n\n7. **Onboarding:**\n   - Once you accept the offer, you will undergo an onboarding process that may include orientation, training sessions, and necessary paperwork.\n\nIt\u2019s important to note that Wipro, like other companies, may adjust their hiring process over time, especially in response to technological advancements or changes in company policy. Networking and referrals can also play a key role in securing an interview, so it\u2019s beneficial to establish connections within the company or industry.",
